      "part_type": "Hadith",
      "path": "/books/al-kafi:2:2:15:8",
      "text": [
        " قَالَ أَبُو عَبْدِ اللَّهِ ( عليه السلام ) إِنْ لَمْ تَكُنْ بِكَ بُكَاءٌ فَتَبَاكَ ."
      ],
      "translations": {
        "en.hubeali": [
          "Muhammad Bin Yahya, from Ahmad Bin Muhammad Bin Isa, from Al Hassan Bin Mahboub, from Anbasa Al Aabid who said, ",
          "‘Abu Abdullah<sup>asws</sup> said: ‘If you cannot be with the weeping, so pretend (try) to weep’."
        ],
        "en.sarwar": [
          "8. Muhammad ibn Yahya has narrated from Ahmad ibn Muhammad ibn ‘Isa from al-Hassan ibn Mahbub from ‘Anbasah al-‘Abid who has said the following: “Abu ‘Abd Allah (a.s.) has said, ‘If you cannot weep then make a weeping-like face.’” "
        ]
      }
